  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span> <strong>red onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/achiote-fish-rice-and-pickled-onions/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>salt</strong> to a bowl with a splash of<strong> boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up until dissolved</p><p>Add the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and <strong>sliced red onion </strong>and set aside to pickle – these are your <strong>pickled onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/achiote-fish-rice-and-pickled-onions/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> basmati rice</strong> and 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/achiote-fish-rice-and-pickled-onions/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, combine the <strong>achiote paste</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> in a large bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>achiote marinade</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>basa fillets</strong> to the <strong>achiote marinade</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the fish is completely covered</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/achiote-fish-rice-and-pickled-onions/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>marinated fish</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through and slightly charred</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/achiote-fish-rice-and-pickled-onions/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the fish is cooking, dice the<strong> remaining red onion</strong></p><p>Dice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>avocado<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, around the stone<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Remove the stone<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> using a teaspoon</p><p>Scoop the <strong>avocado</strong> out of the skin<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span>using a spoon and roughly chop</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/achiote-fish-rice-and-pickled-onions/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped avocado</strong>,<strong> diced red onion</strong> and <strong>tomato</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>juice </strong>of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1] </span><strong>lime</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>avocado salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/achiote-fish-rice-and-pickled-onions/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p><p>Serve the <strong>achiote fish</strong> over the <strong>rice</strong> with the<strong> avocado salsa </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with the <strong>pickled onions </strong>and garnish with a wedge of<strong> lime</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
